        <para>After creating a new subfolder to your "Home" folder, access the new folder by clicking the plus sign in front of your "Home" folder and then select your new folder.
            You can rename the folder: <graphic fileref="images/folder_edit.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;. Enter the new name in the pop-up window.
        .</para>
        <para>To move a folder to another location, click
                <graphic fileref="images/folder_go.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;.
            More on the above actions in the next section.</para>
        <para> You can also delete a folder that belongs to you, 
            in this case the folder you have just created <graphic fileref="images/folder_delete.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;.
            This brings up a dialogue warning that after deleting the folder, the folder and its contents cannot be restored. 
        </para>
        <para> More options are available with 
            <guibutton>Manage Folder Sharing</guibutton> <graphic fileref="images/user_edit.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;. 
            These options are discussed 
            in the section on <ulink href="security-manager.xml">Sharing</ulink>. </para>
        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/walk-through.12.1.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>
        </para>
        <para> The last button&#160;<graphic fileref="images/page_add.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;is to <guibutton>Create Stand-Alone Record</guibutton>. 
            By clicking this button you leave the Tamboti search interface and you are taken to the Tamboti editor, in which you can create a new record. 
            A dialogue window pops up asking you to choose which kind of record you wish to enter.</para>
        <para>If you are in the editor or the dialogue box, you can click <guibutton>Cancel Editing</guibutton> or <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> to return to the search interface.</para>
